# === DOMAIN & EF CORE SAFETY RULES (BỔ SUNG 10/04/2026) ===
# Mục tiêu: Ngăn chặn lỗi duplicate record, sai vị trí using, test DI và bảo vệ kiến trúc kế toán

domain_file_protection:
  target_file: "1_Shared/Domain.cs"
  mandatory_steps_before_edit:
    - "ALWAYS read the ENTIRE file first to check for existing records (LeadId, CustomerId, OrderId, ProductId, etc.)"
    - "NEVER re-declare any record that already exists (CS0101)"
    - "All 'using' directives MUST be at the VERY TOP of the file, before any namespace or class declaration"
    - "EF Core Configuration classes (IEntityTypeConfiguration<T>) MUST be placed at the VERY BOTTOM of the file, inside the namespace"
    - "Value object records (xxxId) must be defined BEFORE their Configuration classes"

ef_core_rules:
  - "All Value Objects used in production or tests MUST have primary key configuration via IEntityTypeConfiguration"
  - "In VanAnDbContext.OnModelCreating, ALWAYS call modelBuilder.ApplyConfiguration(new xxxConfiguration()) for every Value Object"
  - "Never use .HasNoKey() unless the entity is explicitly designed to be keyless"
  - "Global Query Filters for IMustHaveTenant MUST NEVER be bypassed"

test_infrastructure_rules:
  - "When writing tests that inherit IntegrationTestBase: DO NOT create services that depend on Context in the constructor"
  - "Service creation (CustomerService, AccountingService, etc.) MUST happen inside InitializeAsync() AFTER SetupEmptyDatabaseAsync()"
  - "Always implement IAsyncLifetime when database context is required"
  - "Use xUnit correctly: [Fact], Assert.Equal/NotNull/NotNull, never Assert.AreEqual from NUnit"

accounting_module_rules:
  - "All financial/ledger operations MUST be immutable (append-only). Use Reversing Entries for adjustments"
  - "Every AccountingEntry MUST have AccountingBookType, PeriodYear, PeriodMonth"
  - "Direct Update/Delete on AccountingEntry and ElectronicInvoice is STRICTLY FORBIDDEN"
  - "Multi-tenancy (IMustHaveTenant) must be enforced on all new accounting entities"

general_ai_discipline:
  - "When editing Domain.cs, VanAnDbContext.cs or any core file: Read the whole file first → Plan changes → Execute"
  - "If you see CS0246 (type not found) or CS0101 (duplicate), STOP immediately and search the file"
  - "Never append code blindly in the middle of a large file. Always add at correct position (using at top, config at bottom)"

# === ANTI-PANIC & C# SYNTAX GOVERNANCE  ===
- NO PANIC DELETIONS: You are strictly forbidden from deleting or recreating source code files just because they have compilation errors.
- RAW STRING LITERALS MANDATORY: When injecting HTML, JSON, or Javascript, MUST use C# 11 raw string literals (""").
- EF CORE STRICTNESS: Never call .ToList() before GroupBy or aggregations. All aggregations MUST be translated to SQL.

# SMART TEST-DRIVEN DEVELOPMENT (TDD)
1. **Targeted Fast Feedback**: While coding, automatically run ONLY the Unit Tests (Layer 1) related to the modified module (e.g., `dotnet test 6_Tests/VanAn.Core.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~KitchenService"`).
2. **Milestone Verification**: Before completing a major feature, run Integration Tests (Layer 2) and API Tests (Layer 3) to verify cross-module communication.
3. **E2E Delegation**: End-to-End Playwright Tests (Layer 4) are EXPENSIVE. Run them ONLY when completing an entire Epic or User Journey, NOT on every small code change.
4. **Mandatory Unit Tests**: Any new business logic MUST have corresponding Unit Tests.
5. **Anti-Cheat**: DO NOT use `<Compile Remove />` or suppress warnings to pass tests. Fix the code.

